{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"eb06c7e1-998e-4a3f-b01a-ad3bc0f73c56","content":"I don't have a skill for **analyzing** crash dumps (the `dump-collect` skill only covers **collecting** them). However, I can guide you through analyzing it yourself:\n\n### Recommended tools for `.dmp` analysis:\n\n1. **`dotnet-dump analyze`** (cross-platform)\n   ```bash\n   dotnet tool install -g dotnet-dump\n   dotnet-dump analyze your-file.dmp\n   ```\n   Useful SOS commands inside the analyzer:\n   - `clrstack` — managed call stack\n   - `pe` — print last exception\n   - `dumpheap -stat` — heap summary\n   - `threads` — list all threads\n\n2. **WinDbg** (Windows) — load the dump, then:\n   ```\n   .loadby sos coreclr\n   !pe\n   !clrstack\n   ```\n\n3. **LLDB + SOS** (Linux/macOS)\n\n### Want me to try analyzing it here?\n\nIf you upload or provide the path to your `.dmp` file, I can attempt to run `dotnet-dump analyze` on it and extract the exception info, call stacks, and other diagnostics. Just let me know the file location.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"b79ee6e5-dba2-442a-b721-79adef80e115","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user has a .dmp crash dump file from a .NET application and wants to analyze it. Let me check if there's a relevant skill available for this.\n\nLooking at the available skills:\n- `dump-collect` - This is for **collecting** crash dumps, not analyzing them. The description explicitly says \"DO NOT USE FOR: analyzing or debugging dumps, post-mortem investigation with lldb/windbg/dotnet-dump analyze\"\n- `android-tombstone-symbolication` - For Android tombstones, not .dmp files\n- `apple-crash-symbolication` - For Apple .ips crash logs\n\nNone of the available skills are for analyzing .dmp files. The `dump-collect` skill explicitly excludes analysis.\n\n\nSince I don't have a specialized skill for this, I'll provide direct guidance on analyzing the dump file.","outputTokens":480,"requestId":"AC07:2F7C49:148A8E7:1706763:6A0672DA"